==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pipe clay
<hw>Pipe" clay`</hw> <pr>(kl⟦amac⟧`)</pr>. <def>A plastic, unctuous clay
of a grayish white color, -- used in making tobacco pipes and various
kinds of earthenware, in scouring cloth, and in cleansing soldiers'
equipments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pipeclay</ent>⟦br⟧
